        "content": "The analysis ingests posterior samples for the target black holes. For the stellar-mass black hole M33 X-7, the marginalized posterior distributions yield a mass of M_mean ± M_std solar masses and a dimensionless spin of a*_mean ± a*_std. This quantitative characterization of observational constraints forms the fundamental data layer for all subsequent superradiance calculations.",
